==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grolier
<hw>Gro"lier`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The name by which
<person>Jean <etsep>Grolier</etsep> de Servier</person> (1479-1565), a
French bibliophile, is commonly known; -- used in naming a certain style
of binding, a design, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Grolier binding</b></col>, <cd>a book binding decorated
with a pattern imitated from those given covers of books bound for
<person>Jean Grolier</person>, and bearing his name and motto.</cd> --
<mcol><col><b>Grolier design</b></col> <it>or</it> <col><b>Grolier
school</b></col></mcol>, <cd>the pattern of interlacing bars, bands, or
ribbons, with little scrolls of slender gold lines, assumed to be an
imitation of the designs on <person>Jean Grolier's</person> book
bindings.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gromet</ent>⟦br⟧
